docs.abstract: As more suburbanites move downtown, developers are seeking new land for housing and offices, creating opportunities for owners of empty parking lots.
docs.snippet: As more suburbanites move downtown, developers are seeking new land for housing and offices, creating opportunities for owners of empty parking lots.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the lure of urban living pulls more residents from the suburbs, developers are scooping up prime real estate in downtowns across the United States. Soaring property values have created opportunities for owners of an overlooked, underdeveloped asset: the surface parking lot.

headline.main: Parking Lots, Once Asphalt Wasteland, Become Golden Opportunities
headline.print_headline: Prime Urban Lots (Parking Included, of Course)

docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Clint Eastwood received a standing ovation on Tuesday when he was introduced by the Georgia House speaker, David Ralston, for the red-carpet premiere of “Richard Jewell” at the Rialto Center for the Arts in downtown Atlanta. The audience broke into applause again at the climax of the fact-based film Mr. Eastwood directed about the security guard who was suspected by the F.B.I. of planting a bomb at the 1996 Summer Olympic Games.

headline.main: Clint Eastwood’s ‘Richard Jewell’ Is at the Center of a Media Storm
